This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a novel optimization problem for learning Determinantal Point Processes (DPPs) using negative sampling. It also evaluates the proposed method on real-world datasets. The paper also involves the use of negative information, which is commonly used in other machine learning sub-fields such as computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves theoretical and experimental analysis, which is also common in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
